### What DOES Work (Confirmed)
- GPU → ION CMA (WRITECOMBINE) → CPU read: **immediate visibility, no cache sync needed**
- ION_IOC_INV_CACHES with vaddr mismatch: **can flush any userspace VMA page** (vaddr not validated against handle)
- GPU microTLB survives SMMU TLBIALL: **15/15 success**
- Stale TLB write to pinned page: **~85% reliable**
- All kernel addresses known (no KASLR), full vmlinux.elf with 105K symbols

### Why Software Root is Impossible
The fundamental gap: **no way to create a GPU IOMMU mapping to kernel .data physical addresses.** Every IOMMU mapping is controlled by the KGSL driver, which only maps:
- KGSL-allocated pages (buddy allocator, random PAs)
- ION-backed pages (CMA or system heap, fixed/random PAs)
- User pages via MAP_USER_MEM (get_user_pages on user VMAs)

None of these can target PA 0x01648238 (selinux_enforcing). The SMMU registers are on the AHB/APB bus, inaccessible from GPU DMA. CONFIG_DEBUG_LIST blocks the only kernel UAF with known exploit technique.

